data.current_summary: Get the details of a terminal
data.current_description:
Returns the details of a payment terminal, including where the terminal is assigned to. The response returns the same details that are provided in the terminal list in your Customer Area and in the Terminal Fleet report.

>From January 1, 2025 POS Terminal Management API is deprecated and support stops on April 1, 2025. To automate the management of your terminal fleet, use our [Management API](https://docs.adyen.com/api-explorer/Management/latest/overview).
data.description_suggestion: Returns comprehensive details of a specific payment terminal, including its assignment location (merchant account or store), configuration, status, and operational information. The response includes the same terminal information available in the Customer Area and Terminal Fleet report, enabling full visibility into terminal properties and current state.

data.current_description:
Returns a list of payment terminals associated with a company account, merchant account, or store. The response shows whether the terminals are in the inventory, or in-store (ready for boarding or already boarded).

>From January 1, 2025 POS Terminal Management API is deprecated and support stops on April 1, 2025. To automate the management of your terminal fleet, use our [Management API](https://docs.adyen.com/api-explorer/Management/latest/overview).
data.summary_suggestion: Retrieve terminals for an account or store
data.description_suggestion: Returns a list of payment terminals associated with a company account, merchant account, or store. The response includes terminal status information indicating whether each terminal is in inventory, ready for boarding, or already boarded in-store. This operation enables visibility into terminal fleet composition and deployment status across your account hierarchy.
